      "text": "Jensen is in Tokyo this week, where he met with executives from Sega Corporation to commemorate their respective companies' special relationship. In the mid-90s, Nvidia was contracted to design the GPU for the Sega Dreamcast console, but Nvidia couldn't deliver on the contract. This left Nvidia with no revenue and in a precarious position as a young startup. Despite this, Sega decided to give Nvidia a lifeline with a $5 million investment, keeping Nvidia afloat. When the history books are written on how we reached AGI, let's not forget how Sonic the Hedgehog helped us speed run the singularity.",
